    "The convolutional operation is mathematically represented as:",
    "In image processing, f represents the image and g the kernel or filter.",
    "Convolution involves sliding the kernel across the image and computing the dot product at each position, capturing spatial dependencies.",
    "CNNs excel in microfossil analysis due to their translation invariance, which enables accurate fossil identification and classification regardless of their location or variations in imaging conditions.",
